44// macro for doing simple rewrite
45#define TVM_TRY_REWRITE(SrcExpr, ResExpr) \
46 if ((SrcExpr).Match(ret)) { \
47 return (ResExpr).Eval(); \
48 }
49
50// macro for rewrite + recursively rewrite ResExpr
51#define TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(SrcExpr, ResExpr) \
52 if ((SrcExpr).Match(ret)) { \
53 return RecursiveRewrite((ResExpr).Eval()); \
54 }
55
56// macro rewrite only if CondExor is true after match.
57#define TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(SrcExpr, ResExpr, CondExpr) \
58 if ((SrcExpr).Match(ret) && (CondExpr)) { \
59 return (ResExpr).Eval(); \
60 }
61
62// macro rewrite + recursive_rewrite only if CondExor is true after match.
63#define TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE_IF(SrcExpr, ResExpr, CondExpr) \
64 if ((SrcExpr).Match(ret) && (CondExpr)) { \
65 return RecursiveRewrite((ResExpr).Eval()); \
66 }

68// NOTE for developers:
69//
70// We mainly focus on index expression simplification.
71// Besides the RewriteSimplifier, some cases can be better
72// handled by CanonicalSimplifier.
73//
74
75CompareResult RewriteSimplifier::Impl::TryCompare(const PrimExpr& x, const PrimExpr& y) {
76 CompareResult output = CompareResult::kUnknown;
77
78 auto is_finished = [&output]() {
79 return output == CompareResult::kEQ || output == CompareResult::kLT ||
80 output == CompareResult::kGT;
81 };
82
83 output = CompareResult(output & TryCompareUsingConstIntBounds(x, y));
84
85 if (is_finished()) return output;
86
87 if (enabled_extensions_ & kTransitivelyProveInequalities) {
88 output = CompareResult(output & TryCompareUsingKnownInequalities(x, y));
89 }
90
91 return output;
92}
93
94CompareResult RewriteSimplifier::Impl::TryCompareUsingConstIntBounds(const PrimExpr& x,
95 const PrimExpr y) {
96 return TryCompare(x - y, 0);
97}
98
99CompareResult RewriteSimplifier::Impl::TryCompareUsingKnownInequalities(const PrimExpr& x,
100 const PrimExpr& y) {
101 return analyzer_->transitive_comparisons.TryCompare(x, y);
102}
103
104// try to prove x equals val
105CompareResult RewriteSimplifier::Impl::TryCompare(const PrimExpr& x, int64_t val) {
106 PrimExpr diff = this->VisitExpr(x);
107 if (const auto* ptr = diff.as<IntImmNode>()) {
108 if (ptr->value == val) {
109 return CompareResult::kEQ;
110 } else if (ptr->value > val) {
111 return CompareResult::kGT;
112 } else if (ptr->value < val) {
113 return CompareResult::kLT;
114 }
115 }
116 ConstIntBound dbound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(diff);
117 if (dbound->min_value == val && dbound->max_value == val) {
118 return CompareResult::kEQ;
119 }
120 if (dbound->min_value > val) {
121 return CompareResult::kGT;
122 }
123 if (dbound->max_value < val) {
124 return CompareResult::kLT;
125 }
126 if (dbound->min_value >= val) {
127 return CompareResult::kGE;
128 }
129 if (dbound->max_value <= val) {
130 return CompareResult::kLE;
131 }
132 if (val == 0) {
133 ModularSet dmod = analyzer_->modular_set(diff);
134 if (dmod->base != 0) {
135 return CompareResult::kNE;
136 }
137 }
138 return CompareResult::kUnknown;
139}

141void RewriteSimplifier::Impl::Update(const Var& var, const PrimExpr& info, bool can_override) {
142 if (!can_override) {
143 auto it = var_map_.find(var);
144 if (it != var_map_.end()) {
145 ICHECK(ExprDeepEqual()(it->second, info)) << "Trying to update var \'" << var << "\'"
146 << " with a different value: "
147 << "original=" << it->second << ", new=" << info;
148 }
149 }
150 var_map_[var] = info;
151}
152
153PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const AddNode* op) {
154 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
155 op = ret.as<AddNode>();
156 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<Add>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
157 // Pattern var to match any expression
158 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1, b2, s1, s2;
159 // Pattern var match IntImm
160 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2, c3;
161 // Pattern var match FloatImm
162 PVar<FloatImm> c4;
163 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
164 PVar<int> lanes;
165 // Vector rules
166 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
167 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(b1, s1, lanes) + ramp(b2, s2, lanes), ramp(b1 + b2, s1 + s2, lanes));
168 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(b1, s1, lanes) + broadcast(x, lanes), ramp(b1 + x, s1, lanes));
169 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) + ramp(b1, s1, lanes), ramp(x + b1, s1, lanes));
170 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) + broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x + y, lanes));
171 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x + broadcast(c4, lanes), x, c4.Eval()->value == 0.0f);
172 }
173
174 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
175 // Index rules
176 // cancelation rules
177 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x - y) + y, x);
178 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + (y - x), y);
179
180 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x - y) + (y - z), x - z);
181 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x - y) + (z - x), z - y);
182
183 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y - z) + z, min(x + z, y));
184 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x - z, y) + z, min(x, y + z));
185 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y - z) + z, max(x + z, y));
186 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x - z, y) + z, max(x, y + z));
187
188 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x, y + z * c1) + z * c2, min(x + z * c2, y),
189 c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
190 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x, y + z * c1) + z * c2, max(x + z * c2, y),
191 c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
192 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(y + z * c1, x) + z * c2, min(x + z * c2, y),
193 c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
194 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(y + z * c1, x) + z * c2, max(x + z * c2, y),
195 c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
196
197 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) + min(x, y), x + y);
198 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) + max(x, y), x + y);
199 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) + min(y, x), x + y);
200 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) + max(y, x), x + y);
201
202 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x, y + c1) + c2, min(x + c2, y), c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
203 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x + c1, y) + c2, min(x, y + c2), c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
204 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x, y + c1) + c2, max(x + c2, y), c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
205 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x + c1, y) + c2, max(x, y + c2), c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
206
207 // constant folding
208 // NOTE: canonicalization might better at this.
209 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + c1) + c2, x + (c1 + c2));
210
211 // mul co-efficient folding
212 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + x, x * 2);
213 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y + x, x * (y + 1));
214 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x + x, x * (y + 1));
215 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + y * x, x * (1 + y));
216 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + x * y, x * (1 + y));
217 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y + x * z, x * (y + z));
218 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x + x * z, x * (y + z));
219 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y + z * x, x * (y + z));
220 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x + z * x, x * (y + z));
221
222 // DivMod rules
223 // truc div
224 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(truncdiv(x, c1) * c1 + truncmod(x, c1), x);
225 // floor div
226 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floordiv(x, y) * y + floormod(x, y), x);
227 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * floordiv(x, y) + floormod(x, y), x);
228 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floormod(x, y) + floordiv(x, y) * y, x);
229 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floormod(x, y) + y * floordiv(x, y), x);
230
231 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(floormod(x, c2) + c1, c2) + floordiv(x, c2), floordiv(x + c1, c2),
232 c2.Eval()->value > 0);
233
234 // canonicalization rule
235 // will try rewrite again after canonicalization.
236 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + (c1 - y), (x - y) + c1);
237 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE((c1 - y) + x, (x - y) + c1);
238 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + c1 + y, (x + y) + c1);
239 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + (c1 + y), (x + y) + c1);
240 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + max(y, z), max(y, z) + x);
241 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + min(y, z), min(y, z) + x);
242
243 // DivMod rules
244 // truc div
245 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(truncmod(y, c1) + x * c1, x * c1 + truncmod(y, c1));
246 // floor div
247 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(floormod(y, c1) + x * c1, x * c1 + floormod(y, c1));
248 }
249
250 // condition rules.
251 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(select(x, b1, b2) + select(x, s1, s2), select(x, b1 + s1, b2 + s2));
252 // default value
253 return ret;
254}
255
256std::function<void()> RewriteSimplifier::Impl::EnterConstraint(const PrimExpr& constraint) {
257 size_t old_literal_size = literal_constraints_.size();
258 // we will compare the already simplified result with the constraint,
259 // so simplify the constraint as well
260 PrimExpr new_constraint = operator()(constraint);
261 for (const PrimExpr& subconstraint : ExtractConstraints(new_constraint)) {
262 if (SideEffect(subconstraint) <= CallEffectKind::kPure) {
263 literal_constraints_.push_back(subconstraint);
264 // We could apply this during TryMatchLiteralConstraint, but
265 // that would require performing a rewrite of each expression
266 // being checked. This way, we only apply a rewrite for each
267 // constraint being applied.
268 PrimExpr negation;
269 if (subconstraint.dtype().is_bool()) {
270 negation = Not(subconstraint);
271 } else {
272 negation = subconstraint == make_zero(subconstraint.dtype());
273 }
274 negation = operator()(negation);
275 literal_constraints_.push_back(Not(negation));
276 }
277 }
278 size_t new_literal_size = literal_constraints_.size();
279 auto frecover = [old_literal_size, new_literal_size, this]() {
280 ICHECK_EQ(literal_constraints_.size(), new_literal_size);
281 literal_constraints_.resize(old_literal_size);
282 };
283 return frecover;
284}

292PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const SubNode* op) {
293 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
294 op = ret.as<SubNode>();
295 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<Sub>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
296 // Pattern var to match any expression
297 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1, b2, s1, s2;
298 // Pattern var match IntImm
299 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2, c3;
300 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
301 PVar<int> lanes;
302 // Vector rules
303 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
304 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(b1, s1, lanes) - ramp(b2, s2, lanes), ramp(b1 - b2, s1 - s2, lanes));
305 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(b1, s1, lanes) - broadcast(x, lanes), ramp(b1 - x, s1, lanes));
306 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) - ramp(b1, s1, lanes), ramp(x - b1, 0 - s1, lanes));
307 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) - broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x - y, lanes));
308 }
309
310 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
311 // Index rules
312 // cancelation rules
313 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + y) - y, x);
314 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + y) - x, y);
315 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - (y + x), 0 - y);
316 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - (x + y), 0 - y);
317
318 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) - x, min(0, y - x));
319 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) - y, min(x - y, 0));
320 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) - x, max(0, y - x));
321 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) - y, max(x - y, 0));
322
323 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - max(x, y), min(0, x - y));
324 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y - max(x, y), min(y - x, 0));
325 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - min(x, y), max(0, x - y));
326 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y - min(x, y), max(y - x, 0));
327
328 // mul co-efficient folding
329 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - x, ZeroWithTypeLike(x));
330 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y - x, x * (y - 1));
331 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x - x, x * (y - 1));
332 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - y * x, x * (1 - y));
333 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - x * y, x * (1 - y));
334 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y - x * z, x * (y - z));
335 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x - x * z, x * (y - z));
336 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y - z * x, x * (y - z));
337 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y * x - z * x, x * (y - z));
338
339 // constant cancelation
340 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + c1) - c2, x + (c1 - c2));
341 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((c1 - x) - (c2 - y), (y - x) + (c1 - c2));
342
343 // cancelization rule involving 4 operands
344 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + y) - (x + z), y - z);
345 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + y) - (z + x), y - z);
346 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((y + x) - (z + x), y - z);
347 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((y + x) - (x + z), y - z);
348
349 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x + y, z) - x, min(y, z - x));
350 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y + x, z) - x, min(y, z - x));
351 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(z, x + y) - x, min(z - x, y));
352 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(z, y + x) - x, min(z - x, y));
353
354 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x + y, z) - x, max(y, z - x));
355 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y + x, z) - x, max(y, z - x));
356 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(z, x + y) - x, max(z - x, y));
357 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(z, y + x) - x, max(z - x, y));
358
359 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - min(x + y, z), max(0 - y, x - z));
360 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - min(y + x, z), max(0 - y, x - z));
361 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - min(z, x + y), max(x - z, 0 - y));
362 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - min(z, y + x), max(x - z, 0 - y));
363
364 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) - min(y, x), ZeroWithTypeLike(x));
365 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) - max(y, x), ZeroWithTypeLike(x));
366
367 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(b1, b2) - min(s1, s2), b1 - s1,
368 CanProveEqual(((b1 - s1) - (b2 - s2)).Eval(), 0));
369
370 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(b1, b2) - min(s1, s2), b1 - s2,
371 CanProveEqual(((b1 - s2) - (b2 - s1)).Eval(), 0));
372 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(b1, b2) - max(s1, s2), b1 - s1,
373 CanProveEqual(((b1 - s1) - (b2 - s2)).Eval(), 0));
374 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(b1, b2) - max(s1, s2), b1 - s2,
375 CanProveEqual(((b1 - s2) - (b2 - s1)).Eval(), 0));
376
377 // DivMod rules
378 // trucdiv
379 // NOTE: c*(x/c) + x % c == x is true all division mode.
380 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - truncdiv(x, c1) * c1, truncmod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value != 0);
381 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) * c1 - x, 0 - truncmod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value != 0);
382 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - (truncdiv(x + y, c1)) * c1, truncmod(x + y, c1) - y,
383 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
384 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF((truncdiv(x + y, c1)) * c1 - x, y - truncmod(x + y, c1),
385 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
386 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - truncdiv(x - y, c1) * c1, truncmod(x - y, c1) + y,
387 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
388 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x - y, c1) * c1 - x, 0 - truncmod(x - y, c1) - y,
389 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
390
391 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
392 x * c2 - truncdiv(x, c1) * c3, truncmod(x, c1) * c2,
393 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
394 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
395 truncdiv(x, c1) * c3 - x * c2, 0 - truncmod(x, c1) * c2,
396 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
397 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
398 x * c2 - truncdiv(x + y, c1) * c3, (truncmod(x + y, c1) - y) * c2,
399 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
400 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
401 truncdiv(x + y, c1) * c3 - x * c2, (y - truncmod(x + y, c1)) * c2,
402 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
403 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
404 x * c2 - truncdiv(x - y, c1) * c3, (truncmod(x - y, c1) + y) * c2,
405 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
406 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
407 truncdiv(x - y, c1) * c3 - x * c2, (0 - truncmod(x - y, c1) - y) * c2,
408 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
409
410 // Proof in the case of floordiv, need positive condition.
411 // let x = a * c3 + r
412 // (x + c1) / c3 - x / c3 => (r + c1) / c3
413 // NOTE: the use of floormod(c2, c3) was intentional to simplify the const.
414 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + c1, c3) - truncdiv(x + c2, c3),
415 truncdiv(truncmod(x + floormod(c2, c3), c3) + (c1 - c2), c3),
416 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), -c2.Eval()->value) &&
417 c1.Eval()->value >= c2.Eval()->value && c3.Eval()->value > 0);
418 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
419 truncdiv(x + c1, c3) - truncdiv(x, c3), truncdiv(truncmod(x, c3) + c1, c3),
420 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c3.Eval()->value > 0);
421
422 // floordiv
423 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - floordiv(x, c1) * c1, floormod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value != 0);
424 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x, c1) * c1 - x, 0 - floormod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value != 0);
425 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - floordiv(x + y, c1) * c1, floormod(x + y, c1) - y,
426 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
427 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + y, c1) * c1 - x, y - floormod(x + y, c1),
428 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
429 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - floordiv(x - y, c1) * c1, floormod(x - y, c1) + y,
430 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
431 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x - y, c1) * c1 - x, 0 - floormod(x - y, c1) - y,
432 c1.Eval()->value != 0);
433
434 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
435 x * c2 - floordiv(x, c1) * c3, floormod(x, c1) * c2,
436 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
437 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
438 floordiv(x, c1) * c3 - x * c2, 0 - floormod(x, c1) * c2,
439 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
440 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
441 x * c2 - floordiv(x + y, c1) * c3, (floormod(x + y, c1) - y) * c2,
442 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
443 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
444 floordiv(x + y, c1) * c3 - x * c2, (y - floormod(x + y, c1)) * c2,
445 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
446 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
447 x * c2 - floordiv(x - y, c1) * c3, (floormod(x - y, c1) + y) * c2,
448 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
449 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
450 floordiv(x - y, c1) * c3 - x * c2, (0 - floormod(x - y, c1) - y) * c2,
451 c1.Eval()->value != 0 && c3.Eval()->value == c1.Eval()->value * c2.Eval()->value);
452
453 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c1, c3) - floordiv(x + c2, c3),
454 floordiv(floormod(x + floormod(c2, c3), c3) + (c1 - c2), c3),
455 c3.Eval()->value > 0);
456 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c1, c3) - floordiv(x, c3), floordiv(floormod(x, c3) + c1, c3),
457 c3.Eval()->value > 0);
458
459 // canonicalization rule
460 // will try rewrite again after canonicalization.
461 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - c1, x + (0 - c1));
462 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE((x + c1) - y, (x - y) + c1);
463 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x - (y - z), (x + z) - y);
464 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x - y * c1, x + y * (0 - c1));
465 } else if (op->dtype.is_float()) {
466 // Cancellation rules. Deliberately off of the integer path, to
467 // avoid introducing checks on the side effects for the fast path.
468 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - x, ZeroWithTypeLike(x),
469 SideEffect(x.Eval()) <= CallEffectKind::kReadState);
470 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF((x + y) - y, x, SideEffect(y.Eval()) <= CallEffectKind::kReadState);
471 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF((x + y) - x, y, SideEffect(x.Eval()) <= CallEffectKind::kReadState);
472 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - (y + x), 0 - y, SideEffect(x.Eval()) <= CallEffectKind::kReadState);
473 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x - (x + y), 0 - y, SideEffect(x.Eval()) <= CallEffectKind::kReadState);
474 }
475
476 // condition rules.
477 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(select(x, b1, b2) - select(x, s1, s2), select(x, b1 - s1, b2 - s2));
478 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(select(x, y, z) - z, select(x, y - z, ZeroWithTypeLike(z)));
479 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(select(x, y, z) - y, select(x, ZeroWithTypeLike(y), z - y));
480 return ret;
481}
482
483PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const MulNode* op) {
484 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
485 op = ret.as<MulNode>();
486 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<Mul>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
487 // Pattern var to match any expression
488 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1, b2, s1, s2;
489 // Pattern var match IntImm
490 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
491 // Pattern var match FloatImm
492 PVar<FloatImm> c3;
493 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
494 PVar<int> lanes;
495 // Vector rules
496 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
497 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) * broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x * y, lanes));
498 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(b1, s1, lanes) * broadcast(x, lanes), ramp(b1 * x, s1 * x, lanes));
499 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) * ramp(b1, s1, lanes), ramp(b1 * x, s1 * x, lanes));
500 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(broadcast(c3, lanes) * x, broadcast(c3, lanes), c3.Eval()->value == 0.0f);
501 }
502
503 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
504 // constant simplification rule
505 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x + c1) * c2, x * c2 + c1 * c2);
506 TVM_TRY_REWRITE((x * c1) * c2, x * (c1 * c2));
507 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, y) * max(x, y), x * y);
508 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, y) * min(x, y), x * y);
509
510 // Two representations of const*ceildiv(x, c1)
511 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x - floormod(x, c2), c1) * c1, x - floormod(x, c2),
512 c1.Eval()->value == -c2.Eval()->value);
513
514 // canonicalization
515 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x * (c1 * y), (x * y) * c1);
516 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(c1 * x, x * c1);
517 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE_IF((x - y) * c1, (y - x) * (0 - c1), c1.Eval()->value < 0);
518 }
519 return ret;
520}
521
522PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const DivNode* op) {
523 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
524 op = ret.as<DivNode>();
525 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<Div>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
526 // Pattern var to match any expression
527 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1;
528 // Pattern var match IntImm
529 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2, c3;
530 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
531 PVar<int> lanes;
532
533 // x / 2.0 = x * 0.5
534 if (const FloatImmNode* ptr = op->b.as<FloatImmNode>()) {
535 ICHECK(op->dtype.is_float() || op->dtype.is_bfloat16() ||
536 datatype::Registry::Global()->GetTypeRegistered(op->dtype.code()));
537 return op->a * make_const(op->b.dtype(), 1.0 / ptr->value);
538 }
539
540 // Vector rules
541 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
542 // NOTE: use div as the pattern also works for float.
543 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(div(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)), broadcast(div(x, y), lanes));
544 // ramp / bcast
545 if ((div(ramp(b1, c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes))).Match(ret)) {
546 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
547 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
548 ICHECK(c2val != 0) << "division by zero";
549 if (c1val % c2val == 0) {
550 return ramp(div(b1, c2), div(c1, c2), lanes).Eval();
551 }
552 // If all possible indices in ramp are the same.
553 if (CanProveGreaterEqual(b1.Eval(), 0)) {
554 ModularSet bmod = analyzer_->modular_set(b1.Eval());
555 int64_t ramp_min = bmod->base / c2val;
556 int64_t ramp_max = (bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val) / c2val;
557 if (bmod->coeff % c2val == 0 && ramp_min == ramp_max) {
558 return broadcast(div(b1, c2), lanes).Eval();
559 }
560 }
561 }
562 }
563
564 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
565 // Be-aware of the division rules:
566 // We adopt the default C division uses truncation instead of floordiv.
567 // This means most rules need to check non-negativeness of the operands.
568
569 // TryConstFold doesn't work for negative cases because it is also used by legacy
570 // parts of tvm which still assume euclidean div. In this simplifier we assume that the division
571 // is truncated, so perform const folding again.
572 // NOTE: trunc div required
573 if (truncdiv(c1, c2).Match(ret)) {
574 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
575 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
576 return make_const(op->dtype, truncdiv(c1val, c2val));
577 }
578
579 // while it is always true for trunc div
580 // restrict to common case(positive div)
581 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(truncdiv(x, c1), c2), truncdiv(x, c1 * c2),
582 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
583
584 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(truncdiv(x, c1) + c2, c3), truncdiv(x + c1 * c2, c1 * c3),
585 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value >= 0 && c3.Eval()->value > 0 &&
586 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
587
588 if (truncdiv(x * c1, c2).Match(ret)) {
589 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
590 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
591 if (c1val > 0 && c2val > 0) {
592 if (c1val % c2val == 0) return (x * truncdiv(c1, c2)).Eval();
593 if (c2val % c1val == 0) return truncdiv(x, truncdiv(c2, c1)).Eval();
594 }
595 }
596
597 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(truncdiv(x, x), OneWithTypeLike(x));
598 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(truncdiv(x * c1, x), c1);
599 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(truncdiv(c1 * x, x), c1);
600
601 // Rules involving 2-operands.
602 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x * c1 + y, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2) + truncdiv(y, c2),
603 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
604 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
605 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
606
607 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(min(x * c1, y), c2), min(x * truncdiv(c1, c2), truncdiv(y, c2)),
608 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
609 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
610 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
611
612 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(max(x * c1, y), c2), max(x * truncdiv(c1, c2), truncdiv(y, c2)),
613 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
614 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
615 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
616
617 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(y + x * c1, c2), truncdiv(y, c2) + x * truncdiv(c1, c2),
618 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
619 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
620 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
621
622 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(min(y, x * c1), c2), min(truncdiv(y, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2)),
623 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
624 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
625 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
626
627 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(max(y, x * c1), c2), max(truncdiv(y, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2)),
628 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
629 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
630 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
631
632 // Rules involving 3-operands.
633 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
634 truncdiv(x * c1 + y + z, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2) + truncdiv(y + z, c2),
635 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
636 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
637
638 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
639 truncdiv(x * c1 - y + z, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2) + truncdiv(z - y, c2),
640 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
641 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((z - y).Eval(), 0));
642
643 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
644 truncdiv(x * c1 + y - z, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2) + truncdiv(y - z, c2),
645 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
646 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y - z).Eval(), 0));
647
648 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
649 truncdiv(y + x * c1 + z, c2), x * truncdiv(c1, c2) + truncdiv(y + z, c2),
650 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
651 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
652
653 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + c1, c2), truncdiv(x, c2) + truncdiv(c1, c2),
654 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
655 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
656 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
657
658 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + y, x), truncdiv(y, x) + 1,
659 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
660 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(y + x, x), truncdiv(y, x) + 1,
661 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
662
663 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
664 truncdiv((x + y) + z, x), truncdiv(y + z, x) + 1,
665 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
666 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
667 truncdiv((y + x) + z, x), truncdiv(y + z, x) + 1,
668 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
669 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
670 truncdiv(y + (z + x), x), truncdiv(y + z, x) + 1,
671 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
672 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(
673 truncdiv(y + (x + z), x), truncdiv(y + z, x) + 1,
674 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual((y + z).Eval(), 0));
675
676 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x * y, y), x,
677 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
678 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(y * x, y), x,
679 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
680
681 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x * z + y, z), x + truncdiv(y, z),
682 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0) &&
683 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
684 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(z * x + y, z), x + truncdiv(y, z),
685 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0) &&
686 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
687 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(y + x * z, z), truncdiv(y, z) + x,
688 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0) &&
689 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
690 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(y + z * x, z), truncdiv(y, z) + x,
691 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) && CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0) &&
692 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
693 }
694 return ret;
695}
696
697PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const ModNode* op) {
698 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
699 op = ret.as<ModNode>();
700 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<Mod>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
701
702 // Pattern var to match any expression
703 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1;
704 // Pattern var match IntImm
705 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
706 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
707 PVar<int> lanes;
708
709 // Vector rules
710 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
711 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(truncmod(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)),
712 broadcast(truncmod(x, y), lanes));
713
714 // ramp % bcast
715 if (truncmod(ramp(b1, c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes)).Match(ret)) {
716 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
717 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
718 ICHECK(c2val != 0) << "division by zero";
719 if (c1val % c2val == 0) {
720 return broadcast(truncmod(b1, c2), lanes).Eval();
721 }
722 // If all possible indices in ramp are the same.
723 if (CanProveGreaterEqual(b1.Eval(), 0)) {
724 ModularSet bmod = analyzer_->modular_set(b1.Eval());
725 int64_t ramp_min = bmod->base / c2val;
726 int64_t ramp_max = (bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val) / c2val;
727 if (bmod->coeff % c2val == 0) {
728 if (ramp_min == ramp_max) {
729 return ramp(truncmod(bmod->base, c2), c1, lanes).Eval();
730 } else {
731 return truncmod(ramp(truncmod(bmod->base, c2), c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes)).Eval();
732 }
733 }
734 }
735 }
736 }
737
738 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
739 // Be-aware of the division rules:
740 // We adopt the default C division uses truncation instead of floordiv.
741 // This means most rules need to check non-negativeness of the operands.
742 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncmod(x * c1, c2), ZeroWithTypeLike(x),
743 c2.Eval()->value != 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
744
745 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncmod(x * c1 + y, c2), truncmod(y, c2),
746 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
747 CanProveGreaterEqual((x * c1).Eval(), 0) &&
748 CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
749
750 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncmod(x + c1, c2), truncmod(x, c2),
751 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value >= 0 &&
752 c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
753 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
754
755 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncmod(x + y * c1, c2), truncmod(x, c2),
756 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0 &&
757 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0) &&
758 CanProveGreaterEqual((y * c1).Eval(), 0));
759
760 // canonicalization: x % c == x % (-c) for truncated division
761 // NOTE: trunc div required
762 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE_IF(
763 truncmod(x, c1), truncmod(x, PConst<PrimExpr>(make_const(op->dtype, -c1.Eval()->value))),
764 c1.Eval()->value < 0);
765
766 // try modular analysis
767 if (truncmod(x, c1).Match(ret)) {
768 ModularSet mod = analyzer_->modular_set(x.Eval());
769 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
770 if (mod->coeff % c1val == 0 && c1val > 0 && CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0)) {
771 return truncmod(mod->base, c1).Eval();
772 }
773 }
774 }
775 return ret;
776}
777
778PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const FloorDivNode* op) {
779 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
780 op = ret.as<FloorDivNode>();
781 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<FloorDiv>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
782 // Pattern var to match any expression
783 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1;
784 // Pattern var match IntImm
785 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2, c3;
786 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
787 PVar<int> lanes;
788
789 // Vector rules
790 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
791 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floordiv(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)),
792 broadcast(floordiv(x, y), lanes));
793 // ramp // bcast
794 if (floordiv(ramp(b1, c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes)).Match(ret)) {
795 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
796 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
797 ICHECK(c2val != 0) << "division by zero";
798 if (c1val % c2val == 0) {
799 return ramp(floordiv(b1, c2), floordiv(c1, c2), lanes).Eval();
800 }
801 // If all possible indices in ramp are the same.
802 ModularSet bmod = analyzer_->modular_set(b1.Eval());
803 int64_t ramp_min = floordiv(bmod->base, c2val);
804 int64_t ramp_max = floordiv(bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val, c2val);
805 if (ramp_min == ramp_max) {
806 // If b1 can devide c2
807 if (bmod->coeff % c2val == 0) {
808 return broadcast(floordiv(b1, c2), lanes).Eval();
809 }
810 // If all indices can be guaranteed to settle inside a coeff range
811 if (c2val % bmod->coeff == 0 && bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val < bmod->coeff) {
812 return broadcast(floordiv(b1, c2), lanes).Eval();
813 }
814 }
815 }
816 }
817
818 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
819 // Be-aware of the division rules: this is floor division.
820 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(floordiv(x, c1), c2), floordiv(x, c1 * c2),
821 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
822
823 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(floordiv(x, c1) + c2, c3), floordiv(x + c1 * c2, c1 * c3),
824 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c3.Eval()->value > 0);
825
826 if (floordiv(x * c1 + y, c2).Match(ret) || floordiv(x * c1, c2).Match(ret) ||
827 floordiv(y + x * c1, c2).Match(ret)) {
828 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
829 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
830 PrimExpr yval = y.EvalOr(Integer(0));
831 if (c2val == 0) return ret;
832
833 // try eliminate residue part
834 PrimExpr residue =
835 floordiv(x.Eval() * floormod(c1.Eval(), c2val) + floormod(yval, c2val), c2val);
836 PrimExpr y_div = CanProveEqual(floordiv(yval, c2val), 0) ? 0 : floordiv(yval, c2val);
837 auto bound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(residue);
838 if (bound.defined() && bound->max_value == bound->min_value) {
839 return x.Eval() * floordiv(c1val, c2.Eval()) + (y_div + Integer(bound->max_value));
840 }
841
842 // try simplify divisor
843 if (c1val > 0 && c2val > 0 && c2val % c1val == 0 &&
844 CanProveLess(floormod(yval, c2val), c1val)) {
845 // assume c2 == a * c1, x == a * x' + b, y = d * c2 + e then
846 // (x * c1 + y) // c2
847 // ==> ((a * x' + b) * c1 + d * a * c1 + e) // (a * c1)
848 // ==> x' + d + (b * c1 + e) // c2
849 // ==> x' + d since 0 <= b * c1 <= (a-1) * c1, 0 <= e < c1
850 // ==> x // (c2 // c1) + (y // c2)
851 return floordiv(x.Eval(), floordiv(c2val, c1val)) + y_div;
852 }
853 }
854
855 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floordiv(x, x), OneWithTypeLike(x));
856 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floordiv(x * c1, x), c1);
857 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floordiv(c1 * x, x), c1);
858
859 // Rules involving 2-operands.
860 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(min(x * c1, y), c2), min(x * floordiv(c1, c2), floordiv(y, c2)),
861 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
862
863 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(max(x * c1, y), c2), max(x * floordiv(c1, c2), floordiv(y, c2)),
864 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
865
866 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(min(y, x * c1), c2), min(floordiv(y, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2)),
867 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
868
869 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(max(y, x * c1), c2), max(floordiv(y, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2)),
870 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
871
872 // Rules involving 3-operands.
873 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * c1 + y + z, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2) + floordiv(y + z, c2),
874 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
875 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * c1 + y + z, c2), floordiv(x, floordiv(c2, c1)),
876 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
877 c2.Eval()->value % c1.Eval()->value == 0 &&
878 CanProveEqual(floordiv(y.Eval() + z.Eval(), c1.Eval()), 0));
879
880 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * c1 - y + z, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2) + floordiv(z - y, c2),
881 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
882
883 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * c1 + y - z, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2) + floordiv(y - z, c2),
884 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
885
886 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + x * c1 + z, c2), x * floordiv(c1, c2) + floordiv(y + z, c2),
887 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
888
889 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c1, c2), floordiv(x, c2) + floordiv(c1, c2),
890 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
891
892 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * c1, x * c2), floordiv(c1, c2), c2.Eval()->value > 0);
893
894 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + y, x), floordiv(y, x) + 1, CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
895
896 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + x, x), floordiv(y, x) + 1, CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
897
898 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv((x + y) + z, x), floordiv(y + z, x) + 1,
899 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
900 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv((y + x) + z, x), floordiv(y + z, x) + 1,
901 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
902 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + (z + x), x), floordiv(y + z, x) + 1,
903 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
904 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + (x + z), x), floordiv(y + z, x) + 1,
905 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
906
907 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * y, y), x, CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
908 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y * x, y), x, CanProveGreaterEqual(y.Eval(), 0));
909
910 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x * z + y, z), x + floordiv(y, z),
911 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
912 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(z * x + y, z), x + floordiv(y, z),
913 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
914 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + x * z, z), floordiv(y, z) + x,
915 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
916 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(y + z * x, z), floordiv(y, z) + x,
917 CanProveGreaterEqual(z.Eval(), 0));
918
919 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x - floormod(x, c1), c1), floordiv(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value != 0);
920 }
921 return ret;
922}
923
924PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const FloorModNode* op) {
925 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
926 op = ret.as<FloorModNode>();
927 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<FloorMod>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
928
929 // Pattern var to match any expression
930 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, b1;
931 // Pattern var match IntImm
932 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
933 // Pattern var for lanes in broadcast and ramp
934 PVar<int> lanes;
935
936 // Vector rules
937 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
938 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floormod(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)),
939 broadcast(floormod(x, y), lanes));
940
941 // floormod(ramp, bcast)
942 if (floormod(ramp(b1, c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes)).Match(ret)) {
943 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
944 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
945 ICHECK(c2val != 0) << "division by zero";
946 if (c1val % c2val == 0) {
947 return broadcast(floormod(b1, c2), lanes).Eval();
948 }
949 // If all possible indices in ramp are the same.
950 ModularSet bmod = analyzer_->modular_set(b1.Eval());
951 int64_t ramp_min = floordiv(bmod->base, c2val);
952 int64_t ramp_max = floordiv(bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val, c2val);
953 if (ramp_min == ramp_max) {
954 // If b1 can devide c2
955 if (bmod->coeff % c2val == 0) {
956 return ramp(floormod(bmod->base, c2), c1, lanes).Eval();
957 }
958 // If all indices can be guaranteed to settle inside a coeff range
959 if (c2val % bmod->coeff == 0 && bmod->base + (lanes.Eval() - 1) * c1val < bmod->coeff) {
960 return ramp(floormod(b1, c2), c1, lanes).Eval();
961 }
962 }
963 if (bmod->coeff % c2val == 0) {
964 return floormod(ramp(floormod(bmod->base, c2), c1, lanes), broadcast(c2, lanes)).Eval();
965 }
966 }
967 }
968
969 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
970 // Be-aware of the division rules: we use floordiv/floormod here
971 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x * c1, c2), floormod(x * floormod(c1, c2), c2),
972 c2.Eval()->value != 0);
973
974 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x * c1 + y, c2), floormod(x, floordiv(c2, c1)) * c1 + y,
975 c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0 &&
976 c2.Eval()->value % c1.Eval()->value == 0 &&
977 CanProveEqual(floordiv(y.Eval(), c1.Eval()), 0));
978
979 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x * c1 + y, c2), floormod(x * floormod(c1, c2) + y, c2),
980 c2.Eval()->value > 0);
981
982 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x + c1, c2), floormod(x, c2),
983 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value % c2.Eval()->value == 0);
984
985 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x + y * c1, c2), floormod(x + y * floormod(c1, c2), c2),
986 c2.Eval()->value > 0);
987
988 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floormod(x * c1, x * c2), x * floormod(c1, c2), c2.Eval()->value != 0);
989
990 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floormod(x * y, y), ZeroWithTypeLike(x));
991 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(floormod(y * x, y), ZeroWithTypeLike(y));
992
993 // try modular analysis
994 if (floormod(x, c1).Match(ret)) {
995 ModularSet mod = analyzer_->modular_set(x.Eval());
996 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
997 if (mod->coeff % c1val == 0 && c1val > 0) {
998 return floormod(mod->base, c1).Eval();
999 }
1000 }
1001 }
1002 return ret;
1003}
1004
1005PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const MinNode* op) {
1006 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1007 op = ret.as<MinNode>();
1008 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<Min>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
1009
1010 // Pattern var to match any expression
1011 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, s1, s2;
1012 // Pattern var match IntImm
1013 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
1014 PVar<int> lanes;
1015
1016 // vector rule
1017 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1018 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)), broadcast(min(x, y), lanes));
1019 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, broadcast(y, lanes)), broadcast(z, lanes)),
1020 min(x, broadcast(min(y, z), lanes)));
1021 }
1022 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
1023 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, x), x);
1024
1025 // constant int bound
1026 ConstIntBound a_bound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(op->a);
1027 ConstIntBound b_bound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(op->b);
1028 if (a_bound->max_value <= b_bound->min_value) {
1029 return op->a;
1030 }
1031 if (b_bound->max_value <= a_bound->min_value) {
1032 return op->b;
1033 }
1034
1035 // constant comparison
1036 if (min(x + c1, x + c2).Match(ret)) {
1037 if (c1.Eval()->value < c2.Eval()->value) {
1038 return (x + c1).Eval();
1039 } else {
1040 return (x + c2).Eval();
1041 }
1042 }
1043 if (min(x + c1, x).Match(ret) || min(x, x + c1).Match(ret)) {
1044 if (c1.Eval()->value < 0) {
1045 return (x + c1).Eval();
1046 } else {
1047 return x.Eval();
1048 }
1049 }
1050 if (min(c1 - x, c2 - x).Match(ret)) {
1051 if (c1.Eval()->value < c2.Eval()->value) {
1052 return (c1 - x).Eval();
1053 } else {
1054 return (c2 - x).Eval();
1055 }
1056 }
1057
1058 // DivMod rules
1059 // Divide up rounding: truc div
1060 // NOTE: trucdiv(x, y) >= floordiv(x, y)
1061 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, x), x,
1062 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1063 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, max(x, c2)), max(x, c2),
1064 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value &&
1065 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
1066
1067 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x, truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), x,
1068 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1069 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(max(x, c2), truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), max(x, c2),
1070 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value &&
1071 CanProveGreaterEqual(x.Eval(), 0));
1072
1073 // Divide up rounding: floor div
1074 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, x), x,
1075 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1076 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, max(x, c2)), max(x, c2),
1077 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1078
1079 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x, floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), x,
1080 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1081 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(max(x, c2), floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), max(x, c2),
1082 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1083
1084 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(x, floordiv(x, c2) * c2), floordiv(x, c2) * c2, c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1085 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(min(floordiv(x, c2) * c2, x), floordiv(x, c2) * c2, c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1086
1087 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), min(x, y)), min(x, y));
1088 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), min(y, x)), min(x, y));
1089 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), max(x, y)), min(x, y));
1090 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), max(y, x)), min(x, y));
1091
1092 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), x), x);
1093 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), y), y);
1094 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), x), min(x, y));
1095 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), y), min(x, y));
1096
1097 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, max(x, y)), x);
1098 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y, max(x, y)), y);
1099 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x, min(x, y)), min(x, y));
1100 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y, min(x, y)), min(x, y));
1101
1102 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(min(x, y), z), y), min(min(x, y), z));
1103 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(min(min(x, y), z), s1), y), min(min(min(x, y), z), s1));
1104 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(min(min(min(x, y), z), s1), s2), y),
1105 min(min(min(min(x, y), z), s1), s2));
1106
1107 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), max(x, z)), max(min(y, z), x));
1108 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(x, y), max(z, x)), max(min(y, z), x));
1109 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(y, x), max(x, z)), max(min(y, z), x));
1110 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(max(y, x), max(z, x)), max(min(y, z), x));
1111
1112 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), min(x, z)), min(min(y, z), x));
1113 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, y), min(z, x)), min(min(y, z), x));
1114 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(y, x), min(x, z)), min(min(y, z), x));
1115 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(y, x), min(z, x)), min(min(y, z), x));
1116
1117 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y + x, z + x), min(y, z) + x);
1118 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y + x, x + z), min(y, z) + x);
1119 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x + y, x + z), min(y, z) + x);
1120 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x + y, z + x), min(y, z) + x);
1121
1122 // sub distribution
1123 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(y - x, z - x), min(y, z) - x);
1124 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(x - y, x - z), x - max(y, z));
1125
1126 // constant folding rule.
1127 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(min(x, c1), c2), min(x, min(c1, c2)));
1128
1129 // scaling rule
1130 if (min(truncdiv(x, c1), truncdiv(y, c1)).Match(ret)) {
1131 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1132 return truncdiv(min(x, y), c1).Eval();
1133 } else {
1134 return truncdiv(max(x, y), c1).Eval();
1135 }
1136 }
1137 if (min(floordiv(x, c1), floordiv(y, c1)).Match(ret)) {
1138 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1139 return floordiv(min(x, y), c1).Eval();
1140 } else {
1141 return floordiv(max(x, y), c1).Eval();
1142 }
1143 }
1144 if (min(x * c1, y * c1).Match(ret)) {
1145 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1146 return (min(x, y) * c1).Eval();
1147 } else {
1148 return (max(x, y) * c1).Eval();
1149 }
1150 }
1151 if (min(x * c1, c2).Match(ret)) {
1152 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
1153 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
1154 if (c1val == 0) {
1155 return c2val < 0 ? c2.Eval() : c1.Eval();
1156 }
1157 if (c2val % c1val == 0) {
1158 if (c1val > 0) {
1159 return (min(x, c2val / c1val) * c1val).Eval();
1160 } else {
1161 return (max(x, c2val / c1val) * c1val).Eval();
1162 }
1163 }
1164 }
1165
1166 // canonicalization
1167 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(min(min(x, c1), y), min(min(x, y), c1));
1168 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE_IF(min(c1 - x, c2), c1 - max(x, c1 - c2), c2.Eval()->value != 0);
1169 }
1170
1171 // condition rules.
1172 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(min(select(x, y, z), select(x, s1, s2)), select(x, min(y, s1), min(z, s2)));
1173 return ret;
1174}
1175
1176PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const MaxNode* op) {
1177 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1178 op = ret.as<MaxNode>();
1179 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<Max>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
1180
1181 // Pattern var to match any expression
1182 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, s1, s2;
1183 // Pattern var match IntImm
1184 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
1185 PVar<int> lanes;
1186
1187 // vector rule
1188 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1189 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(y, lanes)), broadcast(max(x, y), lanes));
1190 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, broadcast(y, lanes)), broadcast(z, lanes)),
1191 max(x, broadcast(max(y, z), lanes)));
1192 }
1193 if (IsIndexType(op->dtype)) {
1194 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, x), x);
1195
1196 // constant int bound
1197 ConstIntBound a_bound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(op->a);
1198 ConstIntBound b_bound = analyzer_->const_int_bound(op->b);
1199 if (a_bound->min_value >= b_bound->max_value) {
1200 return op->a;
1201 }
1202 if (b_bound->min_value >= a_bound->max_value) {
1203 return op->b;
1204 }
1205
1206 // constant comparison
1207 if (max(x + c1, x + c2).Match(ret)) {
1208 if (c1.Eval()->value > c2.Eval()->value) {
1209 return (x + c1).Eval();
1210 } else {
1211 return (x + c2).Eval();
1212 }
1213 }
1214 if (max(x + c1, x).Match(ret) || max(x, x + c1).Match(ret)) {
1215 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1216 return (x + c1).Eval();
1217 } else {
1218 return x.Eval();
1219 }
1220 }
1221 if (max(c1 - x, c2 - x).Match(ret)) {
1222 if (c1.Eval()->value > c2.Eval()->value) {
1223 return (c1 - x).Eval();
1224 } else {
1225 return (c2 - x).Eval();
1226 }
1227 }
1228
1229 // DivMod rules
1230 // Divide up rounding: truc div
1231 // NOTE: trucdiv(x, y) >= floordiv(x, y)
1232 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, x), truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2,
1233 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1234 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x, truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), truncdiv(x + c1, c2) * c2,
1235 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1236
1237 // Divide up rounding: floor div
1238 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2, x), floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2,
1239 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1240 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x, floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2), floordiv(x + c1, c2) * c2,
1241 c2.Eval()->value > 0 && c1.Eval()->value + 1 == c2.Eval()->value);
1242
1243 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(floordiv(x, c2) * c2, x), x, c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1244 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(max(x, floordiv(x, c2) * c2), x, c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1245
1246 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), max(x, y)), max(x, y));
1247 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), max(y, x)), max(x, y));
1248 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), min(x, y)), max(x, y));
1249 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), min(y, x)), max(x, y));
1250
1251 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), x), x);
1252 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), y), y);
1253 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), x), max(x, y));
1254 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), y), max(x, y));
1255
1256 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, min(x, y)), x);
1257 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y, min(x, y)), y);
1258 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x, max(x, y)), max(x, y));
1259 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y, max(x, y)), max(x, y));
1260
1261 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(max(x, y), z), y), max(max(x, y), z));
1262 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(max(max(x, y), z), s1), y), max(max(max(x, y), z), s1));
1263 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(max(max(max(x, y), z), s1), s2), y),
1264 max(max(max(max(x, y), z), s1), s2));
1265
1266 // max/max cancelation
1267 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), max(x, z)), max(max(y, z), x));
1268 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, y), max(z, x)), max(max(y, z), x));
1269 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(y, x), max(x, z)), max(max(y, z), x));
1270 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(y, x), max(z, x)), max(max(y, z), x));
1271
1272 // max/min distribution
1273 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), min(x, z)), min(max(y, z), x));
1274 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(x, y), min(z, x)), min(max(y, z), x));
1275 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(y, x), min(x, z)), min(max(y, z), x));
1276 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(min(y, x), min(z, x)), min(max(y, z), x));
1277
1278 // add distribution
1279 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y + x, z + x), max(y, z) + x);
1280 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y + x, x + z), max(y, z) + x);
1281 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x + y, x + z), max(y, z) + x);
1282 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x + y, z + x), max(y, z) + x);
1283
1284 // sub distribution
1285 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(y - x, z - x), max(y, z) - x);
1286 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(x - y, x - z), x - min(y, z));
1287
1288 // constant folding rule.
1289 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(max(x, c1), c2), max(x, max(c1, c2)));
1290
1291 // scaling rule
1292 if (max(truncdiv(x, c1), truncdiv(y, c1)).Match(ret)) {
1293 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1294 return truncdiv(max(x, y), c1).Eval();
1295 } else {
1296 return truncdiv(min(x, y), c1).Eval();
1297 }
1298 }
1299 if (max(floordiv(x, c1), floordiv(y, c1)).Match(ret)) {
1300 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1301 return floordiv(max(x, y), c1).Eval();
1302 } else {
1303 return floordiv(min(x, y), c1).Eval();
1304 }
1305 }
1306 if (max(x * c1, y * c1).Match(ret)) {
1307 if (c1.Eval()->value > 0) {
1308 return (max(x, y) * c1).Eval();
1309 } else {
1310 return (min(x, y) * c1).Eval();
1311 }
1312 }
1313 if (max(x * c1, c2).Match(ret)) {
1314 int64_t c1val = c1.Eval()->value;
1315 int64_t c2val = c2.Eval()->value;
1316 if (c1val == 0) {
1317 return c2val > 0 ? c2.Eval() : c1.Eval();
1318 }
1319 if (c2val % c1val == 0) {
1320 if (c1val > 0) {
1321 return (max(x, c2val / c1val) * c1val).Eval();
1322 } else {
1323 return (min(x, c2val / c1val) * c1val).Eval();
1324 }
1325 }
1326 }
1327
1328 // canonicalization
1329 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(max(max(x, c1), y), max(max(x, y), c1));
1330 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE_IF(max(c1 - x, c2), c1 - min(x, c1 - c2), c2.Eval()->value != 0);
1331 }
1332
1333 // condition rules.
1334 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(max(select(x, y, z), select(x, s1, s2)), select(x, max(y, s1), max(z, s2)));
1335 return ret;
1336}
1337
1338Optional<PrimExpr> RewriteSimplifier::Impl::TryMatchLiteralConstraint(const PrimExpr& expr) const {
1339 PrimExpr negation = Not(expr);
1340
1341 ExprDeepEqual expr_equal;
1342 for (const auto& constraint : literal_constraints_) {
1343 if (expr_equal(constraint, expr)) {
1344 return make_const(expr->dtype, true);
1345 }
1346 if (expr_equal(constraint, negation)) {
1347 return make_const(expr->dtype, false);
1348 }
1349 }
1350 return NullOpt;
1351}

1353PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const EQNode* op) {
1354 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1355 op = ret.as<EQNode>();
1356 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<EQ>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
1357 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(ret)) return match.value();
1358
1359 // Pattern var to match any expression
1360 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y;
1361 // Pattern var match IntImm
1362 PVar<IntImm> c1;
1363 PVar<int> lanes;
1364
1365 // vector rule
1366 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1367 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) == broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x == y, lanes));
1368 }
1369
1370 if (IsIndexType(op->a.dtype())) {
1371 CompareResult result = TryCompare(op->a, op->b);
1372 if (result == CompareResult::kEQ) {
1373 return make_const(op->dtype, true);
1374 } else if (result == CompareResult::kNE || result == CompareResult::kGT ||
1375 result == CompareResult::kLT) {
1376 return make_const(op->dtype, false);
1377 }
1378 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - c1 == 0, x == c1);
1379 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(c1 - x == 0, x == c1);
1380 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + c1 == 0, x == 0 - c1);
1381 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x * y == 0, x == 0 || y == 0);
1382 }
1383 return ret;
1384}

1394PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const GTNode* op) {
1395 return this->VisitExpr(op->b < op->a);
1396}
1397
1398PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const GENode* op) {
1399 return this->VisitExpr(Not(op->a < op->b));
1400}
1401
1402PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const LTNode* op) {
1403 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1404 op = ret.as<LTNode>();
1405 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<LT>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
1406 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(ret)) return match.value();
1407
1408 // Pattern var to match any expression
1409 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y, z, s1, s2;
1410 // Pattern var match IntImm
1411 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
1412 PVar<int> lanes;
1413
1414 // vector rule
1415 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1416 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) < broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x < y, lanes));
1417 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(ramp(x, s1, lanes) < ramp(y, s1, lanes), broadcast(x < y, lanes));
1418 }
1419
1420 if (IsIndexType(op->a.dtype())) {
1421 CompareResult result = TryCompare(op->a, op->b);
1422 if (result == CompareResult::kLT) {
1423 return make_const(op->dtype, true);
1424 }
1425 if (result == CompareResult::kEQ || result == CompareResult::kGT ||
1426 result == CompareResult::kGE) {
1427 return make_const(op->dtype, false);
1428 }
1429
1430 // clang-format off
1431 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + y < x + z, y < z);
1432 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x + y < z + x, y < z);
1433 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y + x < x + z, y < z);
1434 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y + x < z + x, y < z);
1435 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y - x < z - x, y < z);
1436 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - y < x - z, z < y);
1437
1438 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x < x + z, 0 < z);
1439 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x < z + x, 0 < z);
1440 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x < x - z, z < 0);
1441 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(c1 < x + c2, c1 - c2 < x);
1442 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(c1 < c2 - x, x < c2 - c1);
1443
1444 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c1 < y * c1, x < y, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1445 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c1 < y * c1, y < x, c1.Eval()->value < 0);
1446
1447 // constant cancelation: only need to make use of one mod
1448 // truc div
1449 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c2 < c1,
1450 x < truncdiv(c1 - 1, c2) + 1, c1.Eval()->value > 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1451 // NOTE: trunc div required
1452 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c2 < c1, x < truncdiv(c1, c2),
1453 c1.Eval()->value <= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1454 // NOTE: trunc div required (euclidean is ok too, floored is not)
1455 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c2 < c1, truncdiv(c1 - 1, c2) - 1 < x, c1.Eval()->value > 0 &&
1456 c2.Eval()->value < 0);
1457 // NOTE: trunc div required (floored is ok too, euclidean is not)
1458 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x * c2 < c1, truncdiv(c1, c2) < x,
1459 c1.Eval()->value <= 0 && c2.Eval()->value < 0);
1460 // NOTE: trunc div required
1461 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < x * c2, truncdiv(c1 + 1, c2) - 1 < x,
1462 c1.Eval()->value < 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1463 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < x * c2, truncdiv(c1, c2) < x,
1464 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1465 // NOTE: trunc div required (floored is ok too, euclidean is not)
1466 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < x * c2, x < truncdiv(c1 + 1, c2) + 1,
1467 c1.Eval()->value < 0 && c2.Eval()->value < 0);
1468 // NOTE: trunc div required (euclidean is ok too, floored is not)
1469 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < x * c2, x < truncdiv(c1, c2),
1470 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value < 0);
1471 // DivMod rules
1472 // trucdiv
1473 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) < c2,
1474 x<c1 * c2, c1.Eval()->value> 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1475 // NOTE: trunc div required
1476 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) < c2,
1477 x<c1*(c2 - 1) + 1, c1.Eval()->value> 0 && c2.Eval()->value <= 0);
1478
1479 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < truncdiv(x, c2), (c1 + 1) * c2 - 1 < x,
1480 c1.Eval()->value >= 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1481 // NOTE: trunc div required
1482 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < truncdiv(x, c2), c1 * c2 < x,
1483 c1.Eval()->value < 0 && c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1484
1485 // invariance for any div mod: x - (x / c1) * c1 == x % c1
1486 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) * c1 < x, 0 < truncmod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1487 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) * c1 < x + y,
1488 0 < truncmod(x, c1) + y, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1489 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x, c1) * c1 < x - y,
1490 y < truncmod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1491
1492 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x,
1493 c2 < truncmod(x + c2, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1494 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x + y,
1495 c2 < truncmod(x + c2, c1) + y, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1496 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(truncdiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x - y,
1497 y < truncmod(x + c2, c1) + (0 - c2), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1498
1499 // floordiv
1500 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x, c1) < c2, x < c1 * c2, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1501 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c1 < floordiv(x, c2), (c1 + 1) * c2 - 1 < x, c2.Eval()->value > 0);
1502
1503 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x, c1) * c1 < x, 0 < floormod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1504 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x, c1) * c1 < x + y,
1505 0 < floormod(x, c1) + y, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1506 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x, c1) * c1 < x - y,
1507 y < floormod(x, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1508 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x,
1509 c2 < floormod(x + c2, c1), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1510 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x + y,
1511 c2 < floormod(x + c2, c1) + y, c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1512 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(floordiv(x + c2, c1) * c1 < x - y,
1513 y < floormod(x + c2, c1) + (0 - c2), c1.Eval()->value > 0);
1514
1515 // canonicalization rule
1516 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(min(x, y) < z, x < z || y < z);
1517 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(max(x, y) < z, x < z && y < z);
1518 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(z < min(x, y), z < x && z < y);
1519 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(z < max(x, y), z < x || z < y);
1520
1521 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x < c1 - y, x + y < c1);
1522 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x < c1 + y, x - y < c1);
1523 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(c1 - y < x, c1 < x + y);
1524 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(c1 + y < x, c1 < x - y);
1525
1526 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x + c1 < c2, x < c2 - c1);
1527 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(x - c1 < c2, x < c2 + c1);
1528 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x - c1 < 0, x < c1);
1529 // clang-format on
1530 }
1531 return ret;
1532}

1534PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const NotNode* op) {
1535 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1536 op = ret.as<NotNode>();
1537 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<Not>(op->a)) return const_res.value();
1538 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(ret)) return match.value();
1539
1540 // Pattern var to match any expression
1541 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y;
1542 PVar<int> lanes;
1543 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1544 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!broadcast(x, lanes), broadcast(!x, lanes));
1545 }
1546
1547 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(!x), x);
1548 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x <= y), y < x);
1549 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x >= y), x < y);
1550 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x < y), y <= x);
1551 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x > y), x <= y);
1552 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x == y), x != y);
1553 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(!(x != y), x == y);
1554 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(!(x || y), (!x) && (!y));
1555 TVM_TRY_RECURSIVE_REWRITE(!(x && y), (!x) || (!y));
1556 return ret;
1557}
1558
1559PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const AndNode* op) {
1560 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1561 op = ret.as<AndNode>();
1562
1563 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<And>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
1564 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(ret)) return match.value();
1565 if ((enabled_extensions_ & RewriteSimplifier::kConvertBooleanToAndOfOrs) &&
1566 !recursively_visiting_boolean_) {
1567 return SimplifyAsAndOfOrs(ret, analyzer_);
1568 }
1569
1570 // Pattern var to match any expression
1571 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y;
1572 // Pattern var match IntImm
1573 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
1574 PVar<int> lanes;
1575
1576 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1577 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) && broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x && y, lanes));
1578 }
1579
1580 auto cfalse = PConst<PrimExpr>(make_const(op->dtype, false));
1581 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x == y && x != y, cfalse);
1582 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x != y && x == y, cfalse);
1583 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x && !x, cfalse);
1584 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x <= y && y < x, cfalse);
1585 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y < x && x <= y, cfalse);
1586
1587 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x < c1 && c2 < x, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value + 1 >= c1.Eval()->value);
1588 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 < x && x < c1, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value + 1 >= c1.Eval()->value);
1589
1590 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x < c1 && c2 <= x, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value >= c1.Eval()->value);
1591 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 <= x && x < c1, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value >= c1.Eval()->value);
1592 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x <= c1 && c2 < x, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value >= c1.Eval()->value);
1593 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 < x && x <= c1, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value >= c1.Eval()->value);
1594
1595 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x <= c1 && c2 <= x, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value > c1.Eval()->value);
1596 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 <= x && x <= c1, cfalse, c2.Eval()->value > c1.Eval()->value);
1597
1598 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x == c1 && x != c2, x == c1 && c1 != c2);
1599 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x != c2 && x == c1, x == c1 && c1 != c2);
1600 return ret;
1601}

1603PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const OrNode* op) {
1604 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1605
1606 op = ret.as<OrNode>();
1607 if (auto const_res = TryConstFold<Or>(op->a, op->b)) return const_res.value();
1608 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(ret)) return match.value();
1609 if ((enabled_extensions_ & RewriteSimplifier::kConvertBooleanToAndOfOrs) &&
1610 !recursively_visiting_boolean_) {
1611 return SimplifyAsAndOfOrs(ret, analyzer_);
1612 }
1613
1614 // Pattern var to match any expression
1615 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y;
1616 // Pattern var match IntImm
1617 PVar<IntImm> c1, c2;
1618 PVar<int> lanes;
1619
1620 if (op->dtype.lanes() != 1) {
1621 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(broadcast(x, lanes) || broadcast(y, lanes), broadcast(x || y, lanes));
1622 }
1623
1624 auto ctrue = PConst<PrimExpr>(make_const(op->dtype, true));
1625
1626 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x == y || x != y, ctrue);
1627 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x != y || x == y, ctrue);
1628 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x || !x, ctrue);
1629 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x <= y || y < x, ctrue);
1630 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(y < x || x <= y, ctrue);
1631
1632 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x < c1 || c2 < x, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value < c1.Eval()->value);
1633 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 < x || x < c1, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value < c1.Eval()->value);
1634
1635 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x <= c1 || c2 < x, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value);
1636 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 < x || x <= c1, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value);
1637 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x < c1 || c2 <= x, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value);
1638 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 <= x || x < c1, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value);
1639
1640 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(x <= c1 || c2 <= x, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value + 1);
1641 TVM_TRY_REWRITE_IF(c2 <= x || x <= c1, ctrue, c2.Eval()->value <= c1.Eval()->value + 1);
1642
1643 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x != c1 || x == c2, x != c1 || c1 == c2);
1644 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(x == c2 || x != c1, x != c1 || c1 == c2);
1645 return ret;
1646}

1648PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const SelectNode* op) {
1649 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1650 op = ret.as<SelectNode>();
1651 if (op == nullptr) return ret;
1652 // Pattern var to match any expression
1653 PVar<PrimExpr> x, y;
1654 TVM_TRY_REWRITE(select(x, y, y), y);
1655 return ret;

1657
1658PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const CallNode* op) {
1659 // add condition context to if_then_else
1660 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1661 op = ret.as<CallNode>();
1662 if (op == nullptr) return ret;
1663
1664 if (op->op.same_as(tir::builtin::likely()) && is_const_int(op->args[0])) {
1665 return op->args[0];
1666 } else if (op->op.same_as(tir::builtin::shift_right())) {
1667 if (op->args[0].as<IntImmNode>() && op->args[1].as<IntImmNode>()) {
1668 // the operator overload will eagerly constant fold.
1669 return op->args[0] >> op->args[1];
1670 }
1671 } else if (op->op.same_as(tir::builtin::shift_left())) {
1672 if (op->args[0].as<IntImmNode>() && op->args[1].as<IntImmNode>()) {
1673 // the operator overload will eagerly constant fold.
1674 return op->args[0] << op->args[1];
1675 }
1676 } else if (op->op.same_as(Op::Get("tir.ceil"))) {
1677 PrimExpr ceil_arg = op->args[0];
1678 if (auto arg_int = op->args[0].as<IntImmNode>()) {
1679 return cast(op->dtype, IntImm(arg_int->dtype, arg_int->value));
1680 } else if (auto arg_float = ceil_arg.as<FloatImmNode>()) {
1681 return cast(op->dtype, FloatImm(arg_float->dtype, std::ceil(arg_float->value)));
1682 } else if (auto arg_call = ceil_arg.as<CallNode>()) {
1683 // ceil(log2(cast(n,"float64"))) is used as the implementation of
1684 // topi.math.ceil_log2, and appears in iteration bounds.
1685 if (arg_call->op.same_as(Op::Get("tir.log2"))) {
1686 PrimExpr log_arg = arg_call->args[0];
1687 if (auto as_float = log_arg.as<FloatImmNode>()) {
1688 // ceil(log2(n)) can be simplified, and should produce the
1689 // same integer result regardless of the target's rounding
1690 // conventions.
1691 return FloatImm(op->dtype, std::ceil(std::log2(as_float->value)));
1692 }
1693 }
1694 }
1695 }
1696
1697 if (op->op.same_as(tir::builtin::likely())) {
1698 // Cases such as for (i, 0, bound) {if (likely(iter_var < bound)) { .. } }
1699 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(op->args[0])) {
1700 return match.value();
1701 }
1702 }
1703
1704 if (op->op.same_as(tir::builtin::if_then_else())) {
1705 // Simplify nested if_then_else
1706 // if (cond) { if (inner_cond) { inner_then_expr } else { inner_else_expr } } else { else_expr }
1707 // => if (cond && inner_cond) { inner_then_expr } else { else_expr }
1708 const PrimExpr& cond = op->args[0];
1709 const PrimExpr& then_expr = op->args[1];
1710 const PrimExpr& else_expr = op->args[2];
1711 const CallNode* inner_call = then_expr.as<CallNode>();
1712 if (inner_call != nullptr && inner_call->op.same_as(tir::builtin::if_then_else())) {
1713 const PrimExpr& inner_cond = inner_call->args[0];
1714 const PrimExpr& inner_then_expr = inner_call->args[1];
1715 const PrimExpr& inner_else_expr = inner_call->args[2];
1716 // Only check constant cases to avoid recursion
1717 if (is_const_number(inner_else_expr) && is_const_number(else_expr) &&
1718 analyzer_->CanProve(inner_else_expr == else_expr)) {
1719 return if_then_else(cond && inner_cond, inner_then_expr, else_expr);
1720 }
1721 }
1722 }
1723
1724 return ret;
1725}
1726
1727PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const VarNode* op) {
1728 Var var = GetRef<Var>(op);
1729 if (op->dtype == DataType::Bool()) {
1730 if (auto match = TryMatchLiteralConstraint(var)) {
1731 return match.value();
1732 }
1733 }
1734
1735 auto it = var_map_.find(var);
1736 if (it != var_map_.end()) {
1737 return it->second;
1738 }
1739 return GetRef<PrimExpr>(op);
1740}
1741
1742PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const CastNode* op) {
1743 PrimExpr ret = IRMutatorWithAnalyzer::VisitExpr_(op);
1744 op = ret.as<CastNode>();
1745 return cast(op->dtype, op->value);
1746}
1747
1748bool RewriteSimplifier::Impl::CanInlineLet(const LetNode* op) {
1749 // Only inline trivial bindings to avoid deep expression explosion
1750 // when we need let to construct complicated expressions.
1751 if (is_const_number(op->value)) return true;
1752 if (op->value.as<VarNode>()) return true;
1753 return false;
1754}
1755
1756PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::Impl::VisitExpr_(const LetNode* op) {
1757 PrimExpr value = this->VisitExpr(op->value);
1758 if (CanInlineLet(op)) {
1759 // it is fine to discard the let binding
1760 // because the value will always be inlined in the simplifier.
1761 analyzer_->Bind(op->var, value);
1762 return this->VisitExpr(op->body);
1763 }
1764 PrimExpr body = this->VisitExpr(op->body);
1765 if (value.same_as(op->value) && body.same_as(op->body)) {
1766 return GetRef<PrimExpr>(op);
1767 } else {
1768 return Let(op->var, value, body);
1769 }
1770}
1771
1772PrimExpr RewriteSimplifier::operator()(const PrimExpr& expr) {
1773 // Run simplification in post order
1774 PrimExpr res = expr;
1775 int max_iter = 2;
1776 for (int i = 0; i < max_iter; ++i) {
1777 PrimExpr new_expr = impl_->operator()(res);
1778 if (new_expr.same_as(res)) return res;
1779 res = new_expr;
1780 }
1781 return res;
1782}

1785 impl_->Update(var, info, allow_override);
1786}
